{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17641016","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17641016"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:21:45+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:21:45+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17855"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17855","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17855"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10569"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78568"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10569","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10569"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17855"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63910"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24641"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24644"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78568","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78568"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EInsulin synthesis involves multiple stages of protein processing within pancreatic beta cells. The formation of disulfide bonds is crucial for proper protein folding and structural stability.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following stages of insulin synthesis involves the initial formation of disulfide bonds?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Proinsulin","Mature insulin","C-peptide","Preproinsulin","Signal peptide"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProinsulin\u003C/strong\u003E is the stage where disulfide bonds are first formed within the endoplasmic reticulum. These covalent bonds are essential for establishing the correct three-dimensional structure of the protein.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMature insulin\u003C/strong\u003E maintains the disulfide bonds that were formed during the proinsulin stage, but does not involve new bond formation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EC-peptide\u003C/strong\u003E is cleaved from proinsulin during processing and does not contain disulfide bonds\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPreproinsulin\u003C/strong\u003E is the initial translation product and has not yet undergone oxidative folding to form disulfide bonds\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESignal peptide\u003C/strong\u003E is removed during transport into the endoplasmic reticulum and does not participate in disulfide bond formation\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe disulfide bonds formed during the proinsulin stage remain present in the final mature insulin molecule and are crucial for its biological activity.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Disulfide bonds are essential for the structural stability and biological activity of insulin.","Disulfide bonds form during the proinsulin stage of insulin synthesis in the endoplasmic reticulum.","The formation of disulfide bonds is a critical step that occurs before proinsulin is cleaved to form mature insulin and C-peptide."],"references":["Bender, D. A., \u0026 Cunningham, S. M. (2021). Introduction to nutrition and metabolism. CRC Press","Salway, J. G. (2016). Metabolism at a Glance. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Chandel NS. Carbohydrate Metabolism. Cold Spring Harb Perspect Biol. 2021 Jan 4;13(1):a040568. doi: 10.1101/cshperspect.a040568. PMID: 33397651; PMCID: PMC7778149"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"